{"ok": true, "lean_translation": "import Mathlib


/-- Let n>0 be an integer and let a,b ∈ Z. Prove that a ≡ b (mod n) if and only if a and b have the same remainder upon division by n. Translate into Lean4 code, ending with := by sorry. -/
theorem modEq_iff_mod_eq {a b n : ℤ} (hn : n > 0) : a ≡ b [ZMOD n] ↔ a % n = b % n := sorry"}
